name: #2 Distress Frequency
description: This picture was taken on a remote place in Georgia. Surrounded by an emptiness one wonders how to call homeUntil 1988, 500kHz was the international Morse Code distress frequency. #2 in the modularmountain series, artwork for bandcamp album found here https://kaotec.bandcamp.com/ The music was inspired on the picture, composed while I was there. The visuals were inspired on the music, overdubbed on the picture. They are dynamic quil patches, live coded in conjunction with live patched modular.
